doc.after: B violacea occurs in southern regions of Western Australia from Woodanilling to Esperance and as far north as Hyden 3 4 This distribution includes areas of the Avon Wheatbelt Esperance Plains and Mallee biogeographic regions 14 It favours white sandy soils often overlying laterite clay or quartzite It usually grows among heath and shrublands associated with mallee eucalypts and Banksia sphaerocarpa var caesia 2 Banksia violacea is classified as Not Threatened under the 1950 Wildlife Conservation Act of Western Australia 14
